                <table style="background-color:#ffd128;" bgcolor="#ffd128" border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK7"><tr><td style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;" styleclass="style_MainTitle" rowspan="1" align="left" colspan="1"><font color="#0c479d" size="5" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;"><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Parenting Tip</span></font><br /></font></td></tr></table>
                <a name="LETTER.BLOCK8" /><table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK8"><tr><td style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;" styleclass="style_MainText" rowspan="1" align="left" colspan="1"><font color="#333333" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;"><div style="text-align: center;">
                    <span style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;" styleclass="style_ArticleTitle"><font color="#0c479d" size="5" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;"><b>

                    Traveling With Kids</b></font></span><br /></div><font style="font-size: 10pt;"></font><br /><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.25in; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">Every child looks forward to their
family's summer vacation. For parents, traveling with children takes planning
and patience, but there are some simple tips to make sure everyone has a great
time.</font><span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></font></p><ul><li><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">Keep kids occupied on a long flight or car ride
by bringing a new bag of toys.<span>&nbsp; </span>Coloring
books, games or toys they've never seen before are more likely to keep their
attention.</font></p></li><li><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">Bring books they haven't read yet or consider a
book on tape if kids are prone to motion sickness.</font></p></li><li><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">Play a game that gets the whole family involved,
such as road trip bingo or the license plate game.</font></p></li><li><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">Make sure to pack plenty of snacks that won't
melt or need refrigeration.</font></p></li><li><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">Schedule down time into your vacation, whether
it's watching a movie or taking a nap, so everyone has energy to enjoy the
day's activities.</font></p></li><li><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">Make sure kids know what to expect when
traveling.<span>&nbsp; </span>Going through airport
security or spending several hours in a car can be daunting if children have
never experienced it before.</font></p></li><li><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: left; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 10pt;">Finally,
remember the reason you went on vacation.<span>&nbsp;
</span>Not to try to do and see as many things as possible, but to relax, have
fun and spend time together as a family.</font></p></li></ul><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt 0.1732in; color: black; text-align: center; font-style: normal; font-weight: normal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;"><font style="font-size: 8pt; color: rgb(12, 71, 157);"><a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" shape="rect" href="#Top">Back to Top</a></font><br /></p></font></td></tr></table>

                
                
                            
                            
                            
