                    <br /></font></td></tr></table><table style="background-color:#ffd128;" bgcolor="#ffd128" border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK17"><tr><td style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;" styleclass="style_MainTitle" rowspan="1" align="left" colspan="1"><font color="#0c479d" size="5" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;"><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Main Article</span></font><br /></font></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK15" /><table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK15"><tr><td style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;" styleclass="style_MainText" rowspan="1" align="left" colspan="1"><font color="#333333" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;"><div style="text-align: center;">
                    <span style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;" styleclass="style_ArticleTitle"><font color="#0c479d" size="5" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;"><b>
                    Walking the Walk</b></font></span><br /><span style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); font-family: Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 14pt;" styleclass="style_ArticleSubTitle"><b>Teaching your Children to be Active</b></span><br /></div><br />Pop quiz for parents!<br />It is important for me to be physically active because...<br />a) I will improve the quality of my sleep.<br />b) I will greatly reduce my risk of health
problems.<br />c) I will keep my thinking, learning, and judgment
skills sharp.<br />d) I will reduce my risk of depression.<br />e) I will set a good example for my child.<br />f) All of the above.<br /><br />Yes, of course, it's all of the above! If the first four
reasons aren't enough to motivate you, think about your child's health. We know
that healthy, active children develop into healthy, active adults. According to

<span style="font-style: italic;">Active Living Research</span>, <span style="font-weight: bold;">physically active children tend to have
better academic achievement than their not-so-active counterparts</span>. Dr.
Steve Sanders of Tennessee Technological University is a strong advocate of
physical activity for children. He points out that daily physical activity
helps them build and maintain healthy bones, muscles, and joints; helps to
control weight, build lean muscle, and reduce fat; prevents or delays the
development of high blood pressure; and reduces feelings of depression and
anxiety. The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention reports that <span style="font-weight: bold;">children and adolescents need at least one
hour of physical activity per day</span>. What's a good way to make sure that your
kids are getting the exercise they need? Get out there with them!<br /><br />Huntsville has some great resources for family summer fun -
here are just a few:<br /><a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" track="on" shape="rect" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1103507962636&s=-1&e=001jxffxxQyu1Jl3csNIimfIZvg2TaRq2NxwxDl954Cy7y732qozOn7-DyaU_M7nfHfKhy8u5zk-qHesg9DNi5F2iFs3sBXoBbMrSnrGobxuEF47ZuuKXllnkQ6vUxKgndT" linktype="link" target="_blank">Monte Sano State Park</a> has picnic areas and a
playground that can provide fun for the whole family, along with hiking trails
for the more adventurous family members. <a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" track="on" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1103507962636&s=-1&e=001jxffxxQyu1KxzuXUluh7UnzQ6oWnRFuhBPbPM2cqGQIueqHetSEDBnnjfcBedmrSmAuV9OBLfV-uRtI-Z9zmih8XyxxoHt9yJHj0dNYVE1z7lpEcq-SeXlFhMwZljGhXxqOeCOxniFw=" shape="rect" linktype="link" target="_blank">Cathedral Caverns</a> provides an
exciting way for little explorers to learn more about Alabama's cave systems. <a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" track="on" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1103507962636&s=-1&e=001jxffxxQyu1JI4d4m7MNYLdHCrurKgZRhOqiXAfV_hGGX2SHLxuJd6joIrbsj0dijNBtBLCMKkyF84R2nLxmtbycJRVjWTthvwPQPFkWXaKp6gtBRfWvUH4cQ4JQz-QCG" shape="rect" linktype="link" target="_blank">Southern Adventures</a> is a local water and amusement park that can bring something new
to your kids' summer routine.<br /><br />Tired of hot weather? Take a few hours to chill with the
family at the <a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" track="on" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1103507962636&s=-1&e=001jxffxxQyu1J9s_PCleKNl6ohcxTRjAygAOthpVGoPD7hhMixxS5pIM8iybjlhmzmvIFxlcOi5b_oDSxI4H4s-fHaZBKJoAjeDjEBsr7Kuo3fNeO2LFc_ww==" shape="rect" linktype="link" target="_blank">Benton W. Wilcoxon Municipal Ice Complex</a>. Sick of the
rain? Head to <a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" track="on" shape="rect" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1103507962636&s=-1&e=001jxffxxQyu1L71-zoBICBnaTLsVHwReeWYqU4C03sWZF0Vru2zgX8CQLF-g6n2uawbrttt1Ng0JhpB1HXJ5-Uqhq5fLPh5ZVvsP0bO4_yLj-CXmYrf4N3gQ==" linktype="link" target="_blank">KidVenture</a>, Huntsville's only indoor playground for kids, where children can climb and play in a safe
and stimulating environment. Trying to save money? Head over to the <a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" track="on" href="http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?et=1103507962636&s=-1&e=001jxffxxQyu1KCed3lbiQ22RdSaOKc2PhXsDwCKbrhLoDpxqgFqICDMB22HfF_FK-FDUmtCInOWNN5cUarS8qjWA_O-Ngcs7YHAgL-8UdVz6sQb2dMp7vEd1HZfdgBQ98bEIFTh4UrBsTRXUqfu-nOow==" shape="rect" linktype="link" target="_blank">Indian Creek Greenway</a> in West Huntsville for bike riding, skating, walking or
playground time.<br /><br />If you're looking for something simpler, try
taking a walk around the neighborhood or playing catch in the backyard.
Whatever you decide to do, teaching your children to have fun while being
active is a gift that will last a (long and healthy) lifetime!<br /><br /><div style="text-align: center;"><font style="font-size: 8pt;"><a style="color: rgb(12, 71, 157); text-decoration: underline;" shape="rect" href="#Top">Back to Top</a></font><br /></div></font></td></tr></table><table style="background-color:#ffd128;" bgcolor="#ffd128" border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK9"><tr><td style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;" styleclass="style_MainTitle" rowspan="1" align="left" colspan="1"><font color="#0c479d" size="5" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" style="color:#0c479d;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:18pt;"><font style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Local Resource</span></font><br /></font></td></tr></table><a name="LETTER.BLOCK17" /><table border="0" width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" id="content_LETTER.BLOCK17"><tr><td style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;" styleclass="style_MainText" rowspan="1" align="left" colspan="1"><font color="#333333" size="2" face="Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif" style="color:#333333;font-family:Trebuchet MS,Verdana,Helvetica,sans-serif;font-size:10pt;"><div style="text-align: center;">

